OL,6,FHe targeted the 94-year-old as he saw
OL,7,Fan opportunity to commit an "easy,
OL,8,Fstraightforward burglary of an elderly
OL,9,Fperson", Detective Inspector Phil
OL,10,FPoole, from West Midlands Police said.
OL,12,FHe returned days later. Wearing a
OL,13,Fbalaclava and carrying a rucksack, he
OL,14,Fgot inside Mr Monk's home as his
OL,15,Fvictim slept.
OL,17,FTopham started to make an untidy
OL,18,Fsearch of the flat but the great-
OL,19,Fgrandfather woke and challenged the
OL,20,Fintruder. It was then that Mr Monk was
OL,21,Frepeatedly beaten.
