OL,6,FShe said the family attended the trial
OL,7,Fto hear Topham's account and
OL,8,Funderstand why he did what he did, but
OL,9,Fsaid his "apparent unfeeling and
OL,10,Fremorseless attitude of the witness
OL,11,Fbox was difficult to experience".
OL,13,FShe ended her statement: "He should
OL,14,Fhave been allowed to grow old and my
OL,15,Fjob was to look after him and make
OL,16,Fsure he was happy the last stretch of
OL,17,Fhis path he had left to go. You
OL,18,F(Topham) took that away from us and
OL,19,Fyou had no right.
